cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with semantic video segmentation using convolutional neural networks. The use of long short-term memory (LSTM) architecture of a recurrent neural network also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of dilated convolution, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for image and video analysis. The paper also deals with multimedia (cs.MM) as it involves the segmentation of video data. Finally, the use of neural networks suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
